<h2>On the homepage</h2>
<div class="vt_img_left vt_small_img"> 
    <span class="top"> </span>
    <span class="bottom"> </span>
   	<img src="/spotlight/innovation/2013-04-01-21century/S_minor-main-standard.jpg" alt="Virginia Tech students Lani Fu, at left, and Jessica Smyth pose with volunteers from a Muslim organization in Sri Lanka." height="122px" width="185px" />
</div><p>Virginia Tech students Lani Fu, at left, a junior majoring in theatre arts and humanities, science, and environment, and Jessica Smyth, a junior majoring in geography,  pose with volunteers from a Muslim organization. Their gift of labor, called Shramadana, is the foundation for Sarvodaya, the largest people's organization in Sri Lanka that networks across 15,000 villages in the war-torn north. Photo by Bob Siegle.</p></div>
